programme.desc: Jenni Yolo helps a young and busy couple make space in their new home. She creates a traditional, formal dining room perfect for sharing meals, as well as spending time with their two young daughters and their extended family.

programme.title: The Story of Home
programme.desc: It's summer in upstate New York and home designers Tara and Percy head outside to work on some projects. They build a Dutch-inspired rock and wood sauna. And Tara works on getting the garden beds ready for next year.

programme.title: The Story of Home
programme.desc: Christmas is here and that means trimming trees and baking cookies. While Tara and Percy get the house ready for the holidays, they renovate the bathrooms. They attempt to make their own tempera paint, but have trouble translating the Swedish directions.

programme.title: The Story of Home
programme.desc: Winter has arrived and it's getting harder to stay warm. Tara and Percy install storm windows to keep out the cold, then renovate the guest and main bedrooms in preparation for a visit from Tara's mom. They struggle stamping a pattern on the walls.

programme.title: The Story of Home
programme.desc: It's summer and time to work on the outside of the house. Tara and Percy paint it a beautiful off-white and enlist the help of friends to build a garden greenhouse. Percy's mom visits to help with the landscaping.

programme.title: Inspired Interiors With Sarah Sherman Samuel
programme.desc: Tackling a personal project, Sarah designs a house intended to show off her portfolio of design work. The show house will feature Sarah's design work inside and out, and allows her to take bigger design risks than with her normal client work.

programme.title: Fixer Upper
programme.sub-title: Family of Five Seeks Open Home
programme.desc: The McKenzies want a new place close to their church, the kids' schools, and a grocery store. Chip and Joanna Gaines help them find a promising house with an open concept and plenty of room for their three kids to play.

programme.title: Fixer Upper
programme.desc: San Diego transplants are on the hunt for their family's dream home in Waco, Texas, and they're looking for a four-bedroom with a large yard and open space for hosting. Their all-in budget of $375,000 leaves them lots of room for substantial renovations, but when faced with a tough decision, they turn to their kids for the deciding vote.

programme.title: Poms
programme.desc: After moving to a retirement community, a woman is inspired to relive her high school days and start a cheerleading team with the fellow residents. The team takes off, but a shocking secret about the captain threatens to derail their training in this comedy film.

programme.title: Second Act
programme.desc: An assistant manager with a stellar record but no college degree makes her unqualified for a big promotion. When a fake resume leads a big financial firm to hire her, it completely changes her life. She then sets out to prove to the world that street smarts matter just as much as, if not more than, degrees and titles.

programme.title: Hustlers
programme.desc: In this delicious dose of cinematic insanity from the director of "Running Scared," a Southern pawn shop connects three outrageous tales involving kidnapping, racist meth heads and an inept Elvis impersonator.
